## Tank Setup

### Size

**Minimum 200 litres** for a single adult. Rope Fish can reach 60–90 cm in length over their 10–15 year lifespan. Long, wide tanks are required for comfortable movement.

### Cover and Hiding

**Dense cover is essential.** Rope Fish are nocturnal and secretive; they spend daylight hours hidden in vegetation, inside pipes, or buried under leaf litter. Without adequate hiding spots they are chronically stressed.

Provide:
- **Large diameter PVC pipes** (10–15cm diameter) — The classic hiding spot; Rope Fish pile into pipes and remain motionless all day
- **Large driftwood structures** with spaces underneath
- **Dense planting** in the substrate margins
- **Leaf litter** — Catappa leaves and other botanicals replicate their natural swamp environment and provide cover; **[available from Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/blogs/knowledge-base)**

### Substrate

Fine sand or smooth substrate. They probe substrate with sensory barbels and move through it; rough substrate damages the barbel area.

### Lighting

Low to moderate. Bright overhead lighting keeps Rope Fish in hiding. Subdued or plant-diffused lighting encourages more visible daytime behaviour.

