## Health

**Respiratory infection:** Breathing difficulty, mucus at the surface, reduced surface breathing frequency. Improve water quality and oxygenation. Veterinary treatment for severe cases.

**Skin injuries:** From rough substrate or tankmate aggression. Heal readily in clean water; treat with clean, warm water and monitor for secondary bacterial infection.

**Internal parasites:** Common in wild-caught specimens. Treat with Praziquantel or Levamisole. Quarantine all new arrivals.

**Wasting disease:** Progressive weight loss despite eating. Internal parasites or bacterial infection. Levamisole treatment; consult a vet if unresponsive.

